# ============================================================
# .gitignore — Family Hub
# ============================================================
# This file tells Git which files to NEVER upload to GitHub.
# Each line is a file or folder pattern to ignore.
# Lines starting with # are comments — Git skips them.
#
# Rule of thumb: anything secret, anything auto-generated,
# and anything that only makes sense on your specific computer
# should be in here.
# ============================================================


# ── SECRETS — NEVER UPLOAD THESE ────────────────────────────
# config.js holds your Supabase URL and API key.
# If this ever ended up on GitHub your database would be
# exposed to the entire internet. This is the most important
# line in this entire file.



# ── MACOS SYSTEM FILES ───────────────────────────────────────
# .DS_Store is a hidden file macOS creates in every folder
# to store icon positions and view settings. It is specific
# to your computer and meaningless to anyone else.
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store


# ── WINDOWS SYSTEM FILES ────────────────────────────────────
# Thumbs.db is a hidden file Windows creates to cache folder
# thumbnail images. Same idea as .DS_Store — computer specific.
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini


# ── VS CODE SETTINGS ─────────────────────────────────────────
# The .vscode folder holds your personal editor preferences
# like font size, theme, and extension settings.
# These are specific to your machine and not part of the app.
.vscode/


# ── NODE MODULES ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# If you ever install npm packages, they go in node_modules/.
# This folder can contain hundreds of thousands of files and
# should never be uploaded — it gets regenerated from
# package.json with a single 'npm install' command.
node_modules/


# ── ENVIRONMENT FILES ────────────────────────────────────────
# .env files are another common way to store secrets.
# We use config.js instead but this covers the pattern.
.env
.env.local
.env.production